         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[The genus  ¶ Donatia ¶  Forst. has similar habit as  ¶ Phyllachne ¶  §  ¶ Helophyllum ¶ . [...] It was until now placed in the Saxifragaceae. Baron Ferdinand von Mueller kindly informed me, however, ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">88.05.00c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Selmar Schönland</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from Schönland (1894), p. 13. The chapter was printed in May 1889; M's letter must have been written before August 1888 since he had had a response to it when, </seg>in M to A. Engler, 16 August 1888, he reported that<seg style=""> Schönland could not believe that </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Donatia">Donatia</name>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style=""> should be moved from Saxifrageae to <name key="Candolleaceae">Candolleaceae</name>. The latest that M could have written to England and received a reply by August is mid-May, and the letter is dated accordingly. Schönland's letter not found.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Die Gattung </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Donatia">Donatia</name>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Forst. hat ähnliche Tracht wie </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Phyllachne</seg>
               <seg style=""> § </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Helophyllum</seg>
               <seg style="">. […] Sie wurde bisher zu den Saxifragaceae gestellt. Herr Baron Ferdinand von Mueller teilte mir jedoch gütigst mit, dass sie nach seiner Ansicht die er schon früher mehrfach ausgesprochen hatte, entschieden zu den C.</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Abbreviation for </seg>
                        <seg style="">
                           <name key="Candolleaceae">Candolleaceae</name>.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> gehört. Ich kann mich dieser Ansicht nicht unbedingt anschließen [...]</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The passage continues with Schönland's arguments for considering </seg>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <name key="Donatia">Donatia</name>
                        </seg>
                        <seg style="">not</seg>
                        <seg style="">to be a genus within <name key="Candolleaceae">Candolleaceae</name>. M's arguments for the transfer are made in B</seg>73.04.02, p. 41.<seg style=""> </seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">]</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; line-height: 0.1945in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[The genus </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Donatia">Donatia</name>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Forst. has similar habit as </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Phyllachne</seg>
               <seg style=""> § </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Helophyllum</seg>
               <seg style="">. [...] It was until now placed in the Saxifragaceae. Baron Ferdinand von Mueller kindly informed me, however, that according to his opinion, which he has already expressed many times previously, it decidedly belongs to the <name key="Candolleaceae">Candolleaceae</name>. I cannot categorically concur with this opinion [...]</seg>
               <seg style="">]</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Candolleaceae">Candolleaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Donatia">Donatia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">Phyllachne <seg style="font-style: normal; ">section</seg> Helophyllum</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
